<HEADLINE>
TAIPEI CITY OFFERS SCHOLARSHIPS TO U.S. CITIZENS STUDYING CHINESE
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Washington, April 29 (CNA) 04/30/07  12:28:44 (By Jorge Liu and
Deborah Kuo)
</P>
<P>
The Taipei City government is offering scholarships to U.S.
citizens who live in American cities and areas that maintain
sisterhood ties with Taipei to learn Chinese in Taiwan, Taiwan's
representative office in Washington, D.C. said in a news release
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The scholarships -- NT$25,000 (US$750) per student -- are part of
Taipei City's efforts to promote "city diplomacy" aimed at
expanding international exchanges, according to the news release
by the Taipei Economic and Cultural Representative Office in
Washington (TECO).
</P>
<P>
A total of 10 applicants from 12 of Taipei City's sister cities
in the United States will be awarded scholarships. The 12 cities
are Houston,  Marshall (Texas) , Dallas, Phoenix, Los Angeles,
San Francisco, Atlanta, Oklahoma City, Boston, Cleveland,
Indianapolis and Guam.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. students who receive the scholarships will take classes
from September this year to next February at the language centers
of National Taiwan University, National Taiwan Normal University
or National Chengchi University.
</P>
<P>
Interested individuals are welcome to visit the Web site of the
Taipei City Education Department at
www.edunet.taipei.gov.tw/public/ ReadNews for more information.
The registration period ends May 22.
</P>
